snippet.textDisplay:
Suraiya Khanum Ji & Anwar Maqsood Sahab,

i am a die hard fan of fold music. Indian and Pakistani folk is the best... I spent more time listening to Pakistani singers... I have immense love for Abida Parveen Ji and Ustad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan Sahab.

Chriyan Da Chamba has been my fav. song... once i listened to your song, i lstopped listening to any other composition. I love both of you very much... I listened to your song for more than 10 times in a row.... and cried all that while... 

i have a sister who is married... i kept thinking about her and cried... i still cant control my tears... 

Love you a lot... Sending you both lot of wishes and Prayers from India

Thanks
Abeer Raj Narayan Singh

snippet.textDisplay: For translation please click MORE --> TRANSCRIPT (for line by line Translation) Excellent folk Song with top quality recitation done by Mr. Anwar Maqsood. For my friends who do not understand the Urdu/Punjabi language. Its a local folk song sung on wedding by bride family. The song is about a letter written from the bride to her father. Letter have a heart touching tone which mixed with Mr. Anwar Masqood voice create an Emotional mix inside any HUMAN BEING able to understand (Sorry from Idiots in advance)
